              <div class="content">
                <h3>Iain Austin</h3>
                <h4><strong>Instrument Procedure Design Specialist | TERPS &amp; PANS-OPS</strong><br>Denver, CO UTC -7 (-6)</h4>
                <div class="column">
                  <p>
                    Iain Austin is the terminal instrument flight procedure design specialist, FAA TERPS &amp; ICAO PANS-OPS, for DragonFly Aeronautics, LLC. In his role, Iain oversees the design development and quality assurance of flight procedure design related to airport and airspace consulting.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    An aviation industry professional with nearly 10 years of experience, Iain is a Commercial, Multi-Engine, Instrument pilot with experience in Part 135 and 121 air carrier operations.  Iain is also a graduate of the Federal Aviation Administration Academy, where he attended Terminal Instrument Approach Procedure development (TERPS) training and ICAO Procedures for Air Navigation Services – Operations Training (PANS-OPS).
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    Prior to joining Dragonfly, Iain also held roles at a major aviation charting and navigation data company providing instrument flight procedure design, performance data calculations and obstacle assessments in support of civilian and military operators.
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="column">
                  <p>
                    Iain works to ensure that DragonFly Aeronautics provides innovative and progressively dynamic solutions to the customer. He is committed to providing customers with efficient and economically effective solutions while ensuring proper compliance to Federal and International aeronautical standards.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    Outside of Dragonfly, Iain is an active general aviation pilot currently pursuing his CFII and enjoys volunteering his time with aviation educational programs.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    Iain holds a Bachelor’s degree in Aviation Management from The Ohio State University and an AAS in Aviation Technology from San Juan College.  
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
